<TITLE> Rice cancels trip to Ghana to handle Middle East </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 WASHINGTON, July 16 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - US Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice has canceled a trip to Ghana this week so that she can stay in Washington for discussions on the Middle East, the State Department said on Monday. Rice had been set to attend an African trade forum in the Ghanaian capital Accra on Wednesday and Thursday but she would now remain in Washington, said her spokesman Sean McCormack. "She thought it was important to be in town here for discussion about a number of different issues, the Middle East, the broader Middle East and Iraq," McCormack told reporters. He said Rice still planned to travel to Lisbon in Portugal for a meeting on Thursday of the quartet of Middle East peace brokers, including new special envoy and former British prime minister Tony Bla
